                         --AMIGADOS GUIDE V2.6--
                                   INFO


   USE:
   Info is used to give detailed information on the filing system and Disk
   devices currently mapped onto your system.

   PATH:
   C:

   SYSTEM:
   2.0, 2.1, 3.0

   EXAMPLES:
   1>INFO
   1>INFO DF1:

   NOTES:
   Once you have executed Info the following headings are present:

   UNIT - The device name.
   SIZE - The amount of formatted storage space available.
   USED - The amount of storage space used in blocks:
          1 block = 512 bytes.
   FREE - How much storage is remaining and available for use.
   FULL - How full the device is as a percentage.
   ERRS - The number of disk errors.
   STATUS - whether the unit is write enabled or not.
   NAME - The name of the disk.

